default49. 
defaultDespite Nigeria’s abundant oil wealth, Nigerians remain among the world’s poorest people
default and the country is set to receive just under £1 billion from the Department for International Development from 2011 to 2015
default. In a country that continues to be plagued by corruption the need for citizen oversight of payments to governments for their natura
defaultl resources is as important as ever. Currently, and as this case demonstrates, detailed information of this nature only comes to light through the accident of court cases in London and New York.
default&#xa0;
